To check if a string is a valid password (minimum length of 8 characters, at least one digit, and one uppercase letter) using `stringr` package in R, follow the steps below:

1. Install the required package: If not already installed, install the `stringr` package by running `install.packages("stringr")`.
2. Load the library: Use `library(stringr)` to load the stringr package.
3. Define a function that checks password validity:

```R
isValidPassword <- function(password) {
  if (nchar(password) >= 8) {
    if (str_detect(password, "[0-9]")) {
      if (any(tolower(substr(password, 1, nchar(password))) %in% letters(c("A": "Z")))) {
        return(TRUE)
      } else {
        return(FALSE)
      }
    } else {
      return(FALSE)
    }
  } else {
    return(FALSE)
  }
}
```

